  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Accumulation of iron in the body\nMost commonly due to hereditary hemochromatosis (HHC) or iron overload from\ntransfusion\nHereditary hemochromatosis most common in people of Celtic ancestry\nAKA \"bronze diabetes\"",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "transfusion",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Transfusion"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Cirrhosis\nDiabetes\ndue to iron deposition in pancreatic beta cells\nCardiomyopathy\nArthritis\n: knuckles of the second and third fingers most common\nBronzing of the skin",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Cirrhosis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Cirrhosis"
        },
        {
          "text": "Diabetes",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Diabetes"
        },
        {
          "text": "Cardiomyopathy",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Cardiomyopathy"
        },
        {
          "text": "Arthritis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Arthritis"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Differential_Diagnosis": {
      "text": "",
      "subsections": {
        "Hepatic_Dysfunction": {
          "text": "Infectious\nHepatitis\nViral hepatitis\nMalaria\nHIV\n(present in 50% of AIDS patients)\n[1]\nEBV\nBabesiosis\n,\nleptospirosis\nTyphoid\nHepatic abscess\n,\namebiasis\nNeoplastic\nMetastases\nHepatocellular carcinoma\nMultiple myeloma\nLeukemia\nLymphoma\nMyeloproliferative disorders\nMetabolic\nHemochromatosis\nWilson's disease\nNon-alcoholic steatohepatitis\nInborn errors of metabolism\nBiliary\nBiliary cirrhosis\nDrugs\nAlcoholic\ncirrhosis\nAlcoholic hepatitis\nHepatotoxic drugs\nMiscellaneous\nOther causes of\ncirrhosis\nAutoimmune hepatitis\nVeno-occlusive disease\nCHF\n(right heart failure)",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Hyperglycemia": {
          "text": "Physiologic stress response (rarely causes glucose >200 mg/dL)\nDiabetes mellitus (main)\nNonketotic hyperglycemia\nHyperosmolar hyperglycemic state\n(HHS/HONC)\nDiabetic ketoacidosis\n(adult)\nDiabetic ketoacidosis (peds)\nCerebral edema in DKA\nDiabetic foot infection\nDiabetic peripheral neuropathy\nHemochromatosis\nIron toxicity\nSepsis",
          "tables": []
